Every foreign key in the tables created only from the entities (not M:N relationship) can mean one of three things:\
-	the foreign key is the primary key at the same time which means that that entity is inherited from an entity with that primary key (in this example there are three inheritances: 1. From User are inherited Student and Company and the User must be either of those but not both of them 2. From Transaction only Owent_transaction is inherited 3. From Item are inherited Service and Product where Item must be either one of them but not both of them )\
-	the foreign key points at a primary key of an entity that has N:1 relationship with it (the foreign key is on the \'93N\'94 side of the relationship)\
-	the foreign key points at a primary key of an entity that has 1:1 relationship with it (the foreign key is on the side that has total participation in the realationship)\
